title: U.S. says it will train Ukrainian pilots to fly F-16s in Arizona
description: The Pentagon’s announcement follows complaints from officials in Kyiv that the F-16 training program was moving too slowly to meet Ukraine’s wartime needs.

title: Russia’s elite draws one lesson from downed plane: Cross Putin and die
description: The downing of Prigozhin’s plane has decisively bolstered Vladimir Putin’s position as a strongman leader.

title: What happened to Putin’s other foes or rivals?
description: It’s still unclear whether Yevgeniy Prigozhin was on a plane that crashed, killing all 10 on board. But he’s not Vladimir Putin’s only foe to suffer a mysterious fate.

title: Somber scenes in Kyiv mark Ukraine’s Independence Day and 18 months of war
description: The mood in the capital felt more subdued than celebratory, as soldiers and civilians reflected on the violence and loss since Russia invaded.

title: Traffic jam at Panama Canal as water level plummets
description: Low water levels, linked to El Niño and climate change, have led authorities to restrict traffic through one of the world’s most important trade arteries.

title: Long after Ethiopia truce, sexual assaults by soldiers continue, says report
description: An analysis of medical records in Tigray showed sexual violence perpetrated by soldiers continued long after the November truce was signed.

title: Putin boosted by Prigozhin’s apparent death, Wagner group future in doubt
description: The possible death of Prighozin and many of his top commanders decapitates the Wagner Group and restores Putin’s reputation after the abortive June mutiny.

title: This startup is storing clean energy in sand. Here’s how.
description: A cadre of startups are building batteries that can store renewable energy in natural materials such as sand, salt and rock.

title: Six countries to join BRICS group; China labels expansion ‘historic’
description: Six countries — Argentina, Egypt, Ethiopia, Iran, Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates — will join the the group in January as Russia and China try to counter the west.

title: Who was on the crashed Russian plane’s passenger list?
description: Those listed on the private jet that crashed in Russia include multiple Wagner associates, including chief Yevgeniy Prigozhin, his deputy Dmitry Utkin, Valeriy Chekalov and Evgeniy Makaryan.

title: What we know about the crashed Russian plane that listed Prigozhin as passenger
description: Yevgeniy Prigozhin and Dmitry Utkin, his deputy in the Wagner mercenary group, were listed on the manifest of a flight that crashed, killing all 10 on board. Here’s what we know.

title: Live updates: No word from Kremlin, Wagner on Prigozhin’s fate after deadly plane crash
description: People in Yevgeniy Prigozhin’s hometown of St. Petersburg paid tributes to him as news of the crash spread, but the Kremlin has not confirmed his death.

title: North Korea says spy satellite launch failed, vows to try again
description: The launch of what North Korea calls a “space launch vehicle,” but is likely a military spy satellite, failed. But Pyongyang vowed to try again in October.

title: Putin rival Prigozhin listed as passenger in deadly plane crash
description: If confirmed, Prigozhin’s death would cap a meteoric rise and fall, coming two months to the day since he launched an audacious challenge to Putin’s rule.
